---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Installation - LrGeniusAI">
  <section class="installation-section">
    <h1>Installation and updates</h1>
    
    <h2>Installation</h2>
    <p>Before you start the installation, please download the latest ZIP file from the <a href="https://github.com/LrGenius/LrGeniusAI/releases" target="_blank">GitHub releases page</a>.</p>
    <p>After the download is complete, extract the ZIP file to your preferred location.</p>

    <h3>Installing LrGeniusAI for the first time</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Open Lightroom Classic.</li>
      <li>Go to <strong>File &gt; Plug-in Manager...</strong></li> 
      <li>Click on the <strong>Add...</strong> button in the lower left corner of the Plug-in Manager window.</li>
      <li>Navigate to the location where you extracted the LrGeniusAI ZIP file. Select the LrGeniusAI.lrplugin folder in it.</li>
      <li>Click <strong>Add Plug-in</strong>.</li>
      <li>LrGeniusAI should now be installed and available in the Plug-in Manager.</li>
      <li>Head to <a href="/help">first steps</a>.</li>  
    </ol>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .installation-section {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  code {
    background-color: #f5f5f5;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
</style>
